  "decision": "Accepted",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. A screening sensitivity analysis was conducted informally during model development to rank material property inputs by influence on construct stiffness; results confirmed that cortical bone modulus and screw-rod interface friction coefficient dominate QoI variance. These findings informed the acceptance criteria tightening to <10% QoI difference. No formal parametric sweep or probabilistic UQ was performed beyond this screening exercise.",
