      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Newton-Raphson residual norm < 1e-5 at each converged load step; energy criterion < 1e-4.",
      "rationale": "All 33 FEA runs (3 solvers × 11 constructs) converged without bisection beyond 3 levels. Residual norms logged and archived. No spurious contact oscillations detected in force-displacement curves. Numerical solver error bounded within acceptable range."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of model setup; checklist-based verification of boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions.",
      "rationale": "Each FEA model was independently reviewed by a second analyst against a documented checklist covering 22 setup items (boundary conditions, material card assignments, contact pair definitions, load application points). Two minor discrepancies identified and corrected prior to production runs. Use error risk assessed as low."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V; frictional contact at screw-rod and screw-vertebra interfaces.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) model calibrated to Ti-6Al-4V coupon tensile data. Frictional Coulomb contact (mu=0.2) at all metallic interfaces. UHMWPE vertebral body surrogate modeled as linear elastic per published modulus range. Model form judged appropriate for the static compression-bending regime up to 40 mm displacement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific coupon testing or peer-reviewed literature; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of test articles.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (113.8 GPa) and yield stress (880 MPa) from lot-specific tensile coupons machined from same bar stock as test screws. UHMWPE modulus (0.94 GPa) from supplier datasheet corroborated by literature. Rod diameter confirmed by CMM (5.5 mm ± 0.01 mm). Screening sensitivity analysis (not formally structured per ASME V&V 40 Appendix C) identified cortical bone surrogate modulus and screw-rod friction as dominant inputs; both constrained by measurement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test constructs from production-representative lots; dimensional inspection confirms geometric fidelity to FEA geometry.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All screws from same production lot (Lot 2021-NC-75); rods from same rod lot. CMM inspection of 3 representative screws confirmed geometry within 0.05 mm of nominal CAD. Sample size sufficient for mean-based comparison with uncertainty quantification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate COU loading environment; multiple load levels or orientations tested.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single compression-bending load configuration per ASTM F1717. Only one test condition (static, room temperature, single offset distance) was evaluated. This factor does not achieve the required level 3; the shortfall is documented and accepted given that the COU is itself the F1717 test configuration, limiting the practical scope for condition variation. Residual risk is mitigated by the large sample size and inter-laboratory confirmation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions demonstrably equivalent to experimental fixture constraints; loading application point and direction matched.",
      "rationale": "Experimental fixture geometry digitized and reproduced in FEA. Load application point (offset 35 mm from rod centerline) and constraint locations matched to fixture drawings. Crosshead displacement rate (25 mm/min) treated as quasi-static; inertia effects negligible. Equivalency confirmed by overlay of FEA deformed shape with DIC images from Lab 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percentage difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy both acceptance criteria across both laboratories. Maximum E/uval = 1.44 (yield force, Lab 2). Maximum percentage difference = 7.1% (yield force, Lab 2). Validation uncertainty uval computed per ASME V&V 20 combining experimental repeatability (s/√N) and FEA numerical uncertainty (GCI-based). Output comparison factor fully satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly correspond to regulatory submission endpoints and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are the primary regulatory QoIs for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions per FDA guidance. Force at 40 mm displacement captures post-yield behavior relevant to fatigue life prediction. All three QoIs are mechanistically linked to the clinical failure mode (screw fatigue fracture at the rod-screw junction). Relevance rated above required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
